Things not to forget for release
1) update configure.ac with the version
2) Run geniustests.pl
3) update help/C/genius.xml with the latest versions
4) run ./update-xml-to-txt-html.sh in help
5) check the .spec file?  Can't test it though probably way out of date.
6) Make genius-function-list.txt for the website (just console output save
   from "help" in the GUI version
7) run ./make-and-upload.sh in help/C (it won't make, that was done before,
   but it will upload)
9) send out release note after the release on the gnome application
   announce forum, note that genius-list no longer works

Tagging stuff:
The name of the tag must be the release number such as 1.0.29
The last commit must be signed git commit --gpg-sign
git evtag sign 1.0.29
git push origin 1.0.29
